  "raw_text": "Additional signing authorities\n\nSigning authority for procurement instruments including the below must be exercised according to the contracting limits, including exceptional authorities as outlined. They include:\n\npurchase orders\n\ncontracts\n\nstanding offers\n\nsupply arrangements\n\nformal agreements and arrangements\n\nstores and supply transfer orders\n\nwritten direction to the agency of record\n\nassignments\n\ngo-ahead letters and messages\n\nletters of intent\n\nconsents to subcontract\n\ntermination for convenience notices\n\namendments to any of the above\n\nAdvance, milestone and progress payments\n\nThe authority for certification of advance, milestone and progress payment claims form PWGSC-TPSGC 1111 (Claim for Progress Payment) is a prerequisite for client certification pursuant to section 34 of the Financial Administration Act is as follows:\n\nUnlimited certification authority applies for incumbents of positions listed in the Table of equivalent positions within AP , with the exception of intern officers/trainees, senior purchasing assistants and procurement assistants.\n\nSenior purchasing assistants have certification authority as follows:\n\nfor contracts beyond their approval authority: claims up to $40,000 with the exception of a final claim or of a release of a holdback\n\nfor contracts within approval authority: all claims\n\nSettlement and release documents\n\nThe authority to sign release and settlement documents (form PWGSC-TPSGC 9223-2 , for terminations on behalf of the Minister of PSPC is delegated as follows\n\narising from a termination for convenience:\n\nDG , Procurement Support Services Sector, AP\n\nDirector, Centralized Services Directorate, AP\n\nfor other than a termination of convenience, PSPC buyers must consult with Finance Branch to determine the appropriate approval authority level\n\nFor assistance on terminations for convenience, consult the Specialized Services for Procurement Division (SSPD) .\n\nContract security\n\nThe Contract Security Program has the authority to provide instructions to contractors concerning compliance with contract security requirements.",
  "markdown_text": "Additional signing authorities\n\nSigning authority for procurement instruments including the below must be exercised according to the contracting limits, including exceptional authorities as outlined. They include:\n\npurchase orders\n\ncontracts\n\nstanding offers\n\nsupply arrangements\n\nformal agreements and arrangements\n\nstores and supply transfer orders\n\nwritten direction to the agency of record\n\nassignments\n\ngo-ahead letters and messages\n\nletters of intent\n\nconsents to subcontract\n\ntermination for convenience notices\n\namendments to any of the above\n\nAdvance, milestone and progress payments\n\nThe authority for certification of advance, milestone and progress payment claims form PWGSC-TPSGC 1111 (Claim for Progress Payment) is a prerequisite for client certification pursuant to section 34 of the Financial Administration Act is as follows:\n\nUnlimited certification authority applies for incumbents of positions listed in the Table of equivalent positions within AP , with the exception of intern officers/trainees, senior purchasing assistants and procurement assistants.\n\nSenior purchasing assistants have certification authority as follows:\n\nfor contracts beyond their approval authority: claims up to $40,000 with the exception of a final claim or of a release of a holdback\n\nfor contracts within approval authority: all claims\n\nSettlement and release documents\n\nThe authority to sign release and settlement documents (form PWGSC-TPSGC 9223-2 , for terminations on behalf of the Minister of PSPC is delegated as follows\n\narising from a termination for convenience:\n\nDG , Procurement Support Services Sector, AP\n\nDirector, Centralized Services Directorate, AP\n\nfor other than a termination of convenience, PSPC buyers must consult with Finance Branch to determine the appropriate approval authority level\n\nFor assistance on terminations for convenience, consult the Specialized Services for Procurement Division (SSPD) .\n\nContract security\n\nThe Contract Security Program has the authority to provide instructions to contractors concerning compliance with contract security requirements.",
